I"^<p>By default, after installing Gentoo Linux, or another distribution, the auto complete in the Shell (in this case we will talk about BASH, however, we will give tips for the other shells) is not installed. Usually you find him on the way:</p>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">/etc/bash_completion
bash_completion.d/<span class="k">*</span>
/etc/bash_completion.d/gentoo-style-init</code></pre></figure>

<p>That is, if you use git, man, ‚Ä¶ You will notice that the next command parameters will not be auto-completed with the [TAB] key.</p>

<p>If you just want to use it at the moment it is, you can use the complete command with the arguments ‚Äòc‚Äô and ‚Äòf‚Äô. Example to auto complete the parameters with the complete command:</p>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"><span class="nb">complete</span> <span class="nt">-cf</span> man</code></pre></figure>

<p>After running this command, you will notice that if you use the man command and a parameter (man [command]) will now appear. Although with this solution appear some observations:</p>

<p>It can auto complete several commands that do not even have manual;
 In other commands there may be an excessive number of possibilities that are not always linked to the command you want.
 When closing the terminal you will notice that the configuration will be lost (but in this case you can add it to your .bashrc, for example echo ‚Äúcomplete -cf [comando]‚Äù¬†¬ª ~/.bashrc).</p>

<p>If you noticed some ‚Äòmess‚Äô in your Shell, you can ‚Äúremove‚Äù with the ‚Äòr‚Äô option this configuration with the command below:</p>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"><span class="nb">complete</span> <span class="nt">-r</span> man</code></pre></figure>

<p>However, the most correct solution is you install an application for Shell, the bash-completion.</p>

<p>To install it, use:</p>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">emerge <span class="nt">--ask</span> app-shells/bash-completion</code></pre></figure>

<p>After installed check that the git, man, ‚Ä¶ commands are auto completing the parameters with the [TAB] key !!!</p>

<p>If you want to see the file, run the command</p>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"><span class="nb">cat</span> /etc/bash_completion.d/gentoo-style-init</code></pre></figure>

<p>For other shells and applications, there are the options below:</p>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">app-shells/zsh-completions
app-shells/tmux-bash-completion
app-shells/mpv-bash-completion
app-shells/gentoo-zsh-completions</code></pre></figure>

<p>For more information, run the Portage search commands:</p>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">emerge <span class="nt">--search</span> completion
emerge <span class="nt">--searchdesc</span> bash-completion</code></pre></figure>

